      "message": "IIUC, this \"-ranchu\" option is currently required for launching an x86/x86_64 AVD with qemu2, but optional for arm64 and mips64. So 1) \"emulator -avd \u003carm64_avd\u003e\" and 2) \"emulator -avd \u003carm64_avd\u003e -ranchu\" should both work for arm64?\n\nNow with this change, the emulator will go look for arm64/kernel-qemu in case 1, but arm64/ranchu/kernel-qemu or arm64/kernel-ranchu in case 2... Is that a problem?",
